'''Kagamine Rin & Len''', a.k.a. '''Kagamine Rin''' ({{lj|鏡音リン}}) and '''Kagamine Len''' ({{lj|鏡音レン}}), is a virtual singer softwear developed by [[Crypton Future Media]](The "Crypton"), based on [[VOCALOID]] by [[Yamaha]]. It's the second work of ''Character vocal series'', which could also be regarded as the anthropomorphic of the softwear.

During the development, Crypton thought to set them as twins that '''Rin is older'''<ref>根津祯 ''実録 開発物語 パソコン用歌声合成ソフト「初音ミク」（最終回）みんなのミクになってみた'', ''日経エレクトロニクス'' (973) [2008.3.10], 日经BP, Page 126-127。</ref>, however when they were released, in order to offer larger space of creation, not only did they gave up the setting of twins, but even the the setting of "Image in the Mirror" was also given up<ref> ''VOCALOIDをたのしもう Vol.2'' Yamaha Music Media, 2009, Page 47</ref>.

Now the setting of '''Kagamine Twins''' has already been accepted by fans and some creators. <del>But "Kagamine Twins" is a '''secondary setting''', accepted by Crypton, but not officially claimed</del>, on the official website of Crypton the library of "VOCALOID2 鏡音リン・レン act2" is also called "超フレッシュなツイン・ボーカル" <ref>https://ec.crypton.co.jp/pages/prod/vocaloid</ref>it's both okay to say Rin is older or Len is older.

