== Kagamine and Road Roller ==

After the release of their character design, since [[Hatsune Miku]], the previous work, was famous for holding a piece of leek in the song [[Ievan Polkka]], many argued for what item should Rin be related to. At the beginning, many said suggested that it could be "yellow or orange fruit or vegetables, such as bananas, oranges, onions, yet none of them were absolutely popular. (Later Both of them had their representative item: orange for Rin, and banana fo Len) On December 1<sup>st</sup> 2007, loadorigin, a niconico user, uploaded [http://www.nicovideo.jp/watch/sm1667273 a video], talking that Rin matches to yellow road rollers, and the onomatopoeia of a road roller, "WRYYYYYYYN!!!" (From "URYYYYYY!!!", the mantra of [[Dio]], who is a charactor in ''[[JoJo's Bizarre Adventure]]'') is similar to the name "Rin". After that, lots of pictures themed road rollers were uploaded on PIAPRO, which is a website built by Crypton for the creators, and the same thing also appeared and became popular on niconico. It at last became one of the representative items of them (Yet banana and orange is more common for fandom creation, and works using road rollers are often comedies. Later in third episode of the official manga ''{{NeedsTranslating|厂商非正式 初音Mix}}'', there's a road roller out of the house where Hatsune Miku and Kagamine Rin and Len lives.

== Their Developement on Multimedia ==

Because of the popularity of their senior, Hatsune Miku, lot's of the costumers wanted Crypton to make CDs, animes and games about them. In October 2007, some companies began to suggest Crpton to make some plannings around these characters, includeing video games, comics, figures, e.t.c. When Kagamine Rin & Len was officially released, different kinds of plannings including Kagamine Rin and/or Len appeared.

On October 25<sup>th</sup> 2007, Comic Rush, a manga magazine, announced that the author of Miku's character design KEI would start to serialize a comic themed Miku named ''Hatsune Mix!'', Rin and Len will appear in Episode 2. Crypton said that it wouldn't be an official work, and they would try to write it in a way so it wouldn't interfer in creation on other worldviews, and it wouldn't be animated at the present stage. When it was officially serializing, the title was changed to ''{{NeedsTranslating|厂商非正式}} Hatsune Mix'', yet the copyright is still Crypton's.

Frontier Works published a fanbook named ''"Hatsune Miku" "Kagamine Rin" CV series Offical Fanbook 2007winter'' on C73. AXIA (Almighty X Item Amusement) and [[COSPA]] would also publish related items. Souvenirs were also sold on C74 in 2008.

Turi Paradise, an online game, had an [http://www.turi-paradise.jp/special/campain1221/ activity] themed Hatsune Miku between December 21<sup>th</sup> 2007 and January 25<sup>th</sup> the next year. Kagamine Rin was added in January 2008, and sang the theme song of the game, ''Water Drop''.

On December 28<sup>th</sup> 2007, [[Niconico Douga]] held a raffle, picked 100 original works using Hatsune Miku, the authors of the works would get the softwear of Kagamine Rin & Len, it ended on January 7<sup>th</sup> 2008, and the result was published on 10<sup>th</sup> that month.

On Feburary 25<sup>th</sup>, Nendoroid of Good Smile Company held a pre-sale of a 10-cm-tall figure of Kagamine Rin. And the face of the figure is solicited from the audience.

{{NeedsTranslating|lang=zh}}

同年6月5日，网络游戏《魔法飞球》继5月22日加入初音未来后，再加入镜音铃于游戏中，活动期间的背景音乐也会改变。6月12日，则再加入镜音连。

同年7月25日，VOLKS开始接受预订镜音铃、连的人物模型，23cm高，母模设计制造为ミルヒ・シュトラーセ，PVC人物模型于2008年11月8日发售，一对10290日圆，已经售罄；树脂人物模型于2009年5月23日发售，一对21000日圆。同日又发表于C74发售混合吧☆天然声音feat.初音未来 1st Anniversary♪，收录初音未来、镜音铃、连、[[MEIKO]]、[[KAITO]]的五首原创曲。

同年8月1日发表NENDOROID造形的初音未来、镜音铃、连预定会出现于世嘉的游戏Virtua Fighter 5R。

同年8月下旬发表制作音乐游戏《初音未来 -Project DIVA-》，镜音铃、连将会在游戏中登场，游戏制作公司会在PIAPRO中征募歌曲、插画和服装设计。

同年9月3日预定发售CD《squarewave surfers～memory of 8bit》，其中会收录一首以act2制作的歌曲《Summertime Blues -『さまたいぶー』》。

同年10月MAX FACTORY预定发售figma系列的铃、连人物模型，铃高约14cm，连高约15cm。

同年10月SEGA推出镜音铃的人物模型，这是选物贩卖机（夹娃娃机）的奖品，镜音连的人物模型（同样是选物贩卖机的奖品）于2010年11月推出。

同年11月5日MOLA Leopalace Z队伍以镜音铃、连痛车（ACG系汽车涂彩）参加SUPER GT11月8日和11月9日于富士Speedway参与SUPER GT该届的最终赛事，在全26队中排名第6，并获得队伍、车手、监督等六项奖状。另外，GOODSMILE RACING亦在2009年1月18日的「FSW新春7时间耐久赛」中使用镜音铃、连痛车为出战赛车之一。

同年11月21日于PIAPRO发表募集迷你四驱车的设计，预定会将获选作品制成迷你四驱车，另又募集迷你四驱车的歌曲。

同年12月27日，乘着镜音铃、连发售一周年，发表在PIAPRO征集歌曲，获选的作品将会由下田麻美翻唱，选拔结果已经公布。

2009年1月28日，初音未来、'''镜音铃、连'''与网站制作软件「IBM Homepage Builder」合作，在合作活动中的购入者可下载专用插画等。

同年6月29日，GOOD SMILE COMPANY发售1/8比例的人物模型，铃高约17cm，连高约16cm，母模设计制造为{{Lang|ja|[http://www.ryunryuntei.com/ 遠那かんし（りゅんりゅん亭）]}}。

